(1748, 'How sophisticated detection stealing money from ATMs', 'How-sophisticated-detection-stealing-money-from-ATMs', '', '1', '<p>Needless ATM card or PIN theft, hackers can still request to release the money ATMs.</p>', '&lt;p&gt;Hackers looking to steal money from ATMs, the main target of the bank card users for years. Specifically, hackers tried to get information access bank accounts by attacking the online service and retail stores. However, a growing number of markets such as the US applied payment methods more secure chip and PIN cards once for mobile payment.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;\n&lt;p&gt;Therefore, instead of trying to steal credit card or imitated them, hackers are trying to take money out of an ATM in a different way, that is poisoning the system software and makes money out of ATMs release at will want.&lt;/p&gt;\n&lt;p&gt;&lt;img class=&quot;news-image&quot; src=&quot;http://anh.24h.com.vn/upload/3-2015/images/2015-09-26/1443277866-1443276843-atm-malware.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;Ph&amp;aacute;t hiện c&amp;aacute;ch thức tinh vi trộm tiền từ m&amp;aacute;y ATM - 1&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;\n&lt;p&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; How sophisticated detection stealing money from an ATM.&lt;/p&gt;\n&lt;p&gt;This is not the first time how destructive such ATMs were discovered, but the level of sophistication was higher. This malicious program called GreenDispenser, the first case was discovered in Mexico, then similar attacks are found in other countries. According to the findings of the security of GreenDispenser, it needs access to ATM hardware to install malicious code, hackers can then start receiving cash and even delete their traces.&lt;/p&gt;\n&lt;p&gt;In addition, ATMs will display an error message but does not affect the hacker stealing money. However, the hacker can easily bypass this error by inserting the correct PIN. Once the PIN is entered into the ATM poisoning, a QR code will be displayed on the screen that the hacker can scan by an application for mobile phones. Then, it will allow the hacker was standing at the ATM machine to activate the release of money.&lt;/p&gt;\n&lt;p&gt;There is a menu option that allows deleting malware safely, helping wipe clean traces and network security companies could not recover&lt;/p&gt;', 1, 0, '', 0, '', '', '1487835298.jpg', '23022017143458', 0, 635, 1, 2, '2017-02-23 14:34:58', NULL, 142, NULL, 0),
